Name: Observation_Information
Description: The Observation_Information class provides information about a science observation.

Name: release_number
Description: release_number is the identifier of a scheduled release of Mars 2020 data from PDS. The first Mars 2020 data release has release_number "01". The release_number for a given product is always the first release in which it appears, and does not change if the product is revised later.

Name: mission_phase_name
Description: The mission_phase_name identifies a time period within the mission.

Name: ATLO
Description: The ATLO mission phase (Assembly, Test, and Launch Operations) is the time of spacecraft and instrument assembly and test. During this phase data products are generated using flight hardware. They are usually not part of the final PDS archive but may be used for testing and peer review.

Name: Cruise
Description: The cruise mission phase is from the time of escape from Earth's orbit through the time of entry into Mars' orbit. Some data products may be generated during this time, including instrument checkout data.

Name: Development
Description: The development mission phase refers to the period of data processing software development and testing, before instruments are integrated with the spacecraft. Data products generated during this phase are usually not part of the final PDS archive but may be used for testing and peer review.

Name: Surface Mission
Description: The surface mission phase is the time from arrival at Mars through the end of surface operations, including the primary mission and any extended missions that may take place.

Name: Test
Description: The test mission phase is not a time period but a placeholder for the mission_phase_name value, used for test data products.

Name: product_type_name
Description: The product_type_name identifies a group of data products within a collection that have some property in common, such as processing level, resolution, or instrument-specific setting.

Name: spacecraft_clock_start
Description: The spacecraft_clock_start is the value of the spacecraft clock at the beginning of an observation, in seconds. Values are formed according to the pattern [p/]dddddddddd[.fffffffff], where p is an optional partition number, dddddddddd is a whole number of seconds up to 10 digits, and .fffffffff is an optional fraction of a second up to 9 digits. The whole number and fraction are separated by a period. If a partition number and slash are not present, then the attribute spacecraft_clock_partition must be used.

Name: spacecraft_clock_stop
Description: The spacecraft_clock_stop is the value of the spacecraft clock at the end of an observation, in seconds. Values are formed according to the pattern [p/]dddddddddd[.fffffffff], where p is an optional partition number, dddddddddd is a whole number of seconds up to 10 digits, and .fffffffff is an optional fraction of a second up to 9 digits. The whole number and fraction are separated by a period. If a partition number and slash are not present, then the attribute spacecraft_clock_partition must be used.

Name: spacecraft_clock_partition
Description: The spacecraft_clock_partition provides the clock partition active for the spacecraft_clock_start and spacecraft_clock_stop attributes. This attribute may be used when the spacecraft_clock values do not include a partition number.

Name: sol_number
Description: Sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which an observation was acquired. Landing day is Sol 0.

Name: start_sol_number
Description: Start_sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which a multiple-day observation was begun. Landing day is Sol 0.

Name: stop_sol_number
Description: Stop_sol_number is the number of the Mars day on which a multiple-day observation was ended. Landing day is Sol 0.

Name: start_local_mean_solar_time
Description: Start_local_mean_solar_time is the local mean solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.

Name: stop_local_mean_solar_time
Description: Stop_local_mean_solar_time is the local mean solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.

Name: start_local_true_solar_time
Description: Start_local_true_solar_time is the local true solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.

Name: start_local_true_solar_time_sol
Description: The start_local_true_solar_time_sol element specifies the number of solar days elapsed since a reference day (e.g. the day on which a landing vehicle set down) for local true solar time (LTST). Days are measured in rotations of the planet in question from midnight to midnight. The reference day is '0', as Landing day is Sol 0. If before Landing day, then value will be less than or equal to '0' and can be negative. Start_local_true_solar_time_sol should accompany the attribute start_local_true_solar_time if that attribute's value does not include a sol number prefix.

Name: stop_local_true_solar_time
Description: Stop_local_true_solar_time is the local true solar time, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.

Name: stop_local_true_solar_time_sol
Description: The stop_local_true_solar_time_sol element specifies the number of solar days elapsed since a reference day (e.g. the day on which a landing vehicle set down) for local true solar time (LTST). Days are measured in rotations of the planet in question from midnight to midnight. The reference day is '0', as Landing day is Sol 0. If before Landing day, then value will be less than or equal to '0' and can be negative. Stop_local_true_solar_time_sol should accompany the attribute stop_local_true_solar_time if that attribute's value does not include a sol number prefix.

Name: start_solar_longitude
Description: Start_solar_longitude is the solar longitude, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the beginning of an observation.

Name: stop_solar_longitude
Description: Stop_solar_longitude is the solar longitude, as defined in the main PDS4 data dictionary, at the end of an observation.

Name: active_flight_computer
Description: The active_flight_computer indicates which flight computer "string" (separate sets of electronics) was active when a product was acquired. For Mars 2020 there are two redundant flight computers called "strings", also known as Rover Compute Elements (RCEs). Either string, A or B, may be active at any given time.

Name: A
Description: The value "A" indicates flight computer A.

Name: B
Description: The value "B" indicates flight computer B.

Name: start_mars_year
Description: The start_mars_year element gives the Mars year at the beginning of the observation. Mars Year 1 began on April 11, 1955. The year number is incremented by 1 for each Martian spring equinox (solar longitude 0 degrees).

Name: stop_mars_year
Description: The stop_mars_year element gives the Mars year at the end of the observation. Mars Year 1 began on April 11, 1955. The year number is incremented by 1 for each Martian spring equinox (solar longitude 0 degrees).

Name: Run_Parameter_Table_Field
Description: MOXIE Run Parameter Table Field

Name: name
Description: The name attribute provides a word or combination of words by which the object is known.

Name: description
Description: The description attribute provides a statement, picture in words, or account that describes or is otherwise relevant to the object.

Name: unit
Description: The unit attribute provides the unit of measurement.

Name: Run_Parameter_Table_Fields
Description: MOXIE Run Parameter Table Fields

Name: Run_Parameter_Table_Values
Description: MOXIE Run Parameter Table Values

Name: persistence_en
Description: For MOXIE: MOXIE_Parameters persistence time enable flag

Name: tl_ics1234_h_calibrated
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensors CS1, CS2, CS3 and CS4 upper temperature limit in calibrated units

Name: tl_ics1234_h_digital_number
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensors CS1, CS2, CS3 and CS4 upper temperature limit in digital numbers

Name: cl_ics123_h_calibrated
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensors CS1, CS2 and CS3 upper current limit in calibrated units

Name: cl_ics123_h_digital_number
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensors CS1, CS2 and CS3 upper current limit in digital numbers

Name: cl_ics4_h_calibrated
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensor CS4 upper current limit in calibrated units

Name: cl_ics4_h_digital_number
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensor CS4 upper current limit in digital numbers

Name: tl_ics1234_t
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensors CS1, CS2, CS3 and CS4 temperature limit persistence time

Name: cl_ics123_t
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensors CS1, CS2 and CS3 current limit persistence time

Name: cl_ics4_t
Description: For MOXIE: Gas composition sensor CS4 current limit persistence time

Name: Run_Parameter_Table
Description: MOXIE Run Parameter Table

Name: Experiment_Configuration_Metadata
Description: MOXIE Experiment Configuration Metadata

Name: run_id
Description: For MOXIE: Unique identifier for the experiment configuration

Name: experiment_name
Description: For MOXIE: Name of a MOXIE_Parameters experiment configuration

Name: major_version_number
Description: For MOXIE: Major version number of the experiment configuration

Name: minor_version_number
Description: For MOXIE: Minor version number of the experiment configuration

Name: file_name_stem
Description: For MOXIE: Stem of the file names used when creating the experiment configuration

Name: primary_objective
Description: For MOXIE: Primary objective of the experiment configuration

Name: secondary_objective
Description: For MOXIE: Secondary objective of the experiment configuration

Name: Experiment_Configuration
Description: MOXIE Experiment Configuration

Name: Digital_Number_To_Calibrated_Unit_Constant
Description: Digital number to calibrated unit constant

Name: symbol
Description: Symbol of the constant in the digital number to calibrated unit equation

Name: value
Description: Numerical value of the constant in the digital number to calibrated unit equation

Name: Digital_Number_To_Calibrated_Unit_Equation
Description: Digital number to calibrated unit equation

Name: parameter
Description: Name of the field to which the digital number to calibrated unit equation applies

Name: equation
Description: Digital number to calibrated unit equation

Name: Digital_Number_To_Calibrated_Unit_Equations
Description: Digital number to calibrated unit equations

Name: comments
Description: Comments associated with MOXIE_Parameters/Run_Control_Table_Step or with MOXIE_Parameters/.../Digital_Number_To_Calibrated_Unit_Equations.

Name: Digital_Number_To_Calibrated_Unit_Conversions_Metadata
Description: Digital number to calibrated unit conversions metadata

Name: file_name_calibration_table
Description: Name of the calibration table file containing the digital number to calibrated unit conversions

Name: file_name_standard_parameters
Description: Name of the file containing the mapping from parameters to digital number to calibrated unit conversions, for parameters in standard telemetry

Name: file_name_extended_parameters
Description: Name of the file containing the mapping from parameters to digital number to calibrated unit conversions, for parameters in extended telemetry

Name: file_name_derived_parameters
Description: Name of the file containing the mapping from parameters to digital number to calibrated unit conversions, for parameters not in telemetry

Name: digital_number_to_calibrated_unit_conversion_software_version
Description: Version number of the software used to convert digital numbers to calibrated units

Name: Digital_Number_To_Calibrated_Unit_Conversions
Description: Digital number to calibrated unit conversions

Name: Ancillary_Data_MEDA
Description: References to ancillary data acquired by the MEDA instrument

Name: Ancillary_Data_Supercam
Description: References to ancillary data acquired by the Supercam instrument microphone

Name: Ancillary_Data_EDLCAM
Description: References to ancillary data acquired by the EDLCam instrument microphone

Name: Ancillary_Data_Rover
Description: References to ancillary data acquired by the rover

Name: Ancillary_Data
Description: References to ancillary data acquired by other instruments and/or the rover

Name: MOXIE_Parameters
Description: The MOXIE_Parameters class provides metadata specific to MOXIE observations.

Name: Device_Current
Description: The Device_Current class provides the current of some point on an imaging instrument or other imaging device.

Name: device_name
Description: The device_name attribute supplies the formal name for an imaging instrument, an imaging instrument device, or some point on the instrument or device.

Name: current_value
Description: The current_value attribute provides provides the current, in the specified units, of an imaging instrument or some part of the imaging instrument.

Name: Device_Currents
Description: The Device_Currents class provides a container for the set of currents of an imaging instrument or other imaging device.

Name: Device_Flash
Description: The Device_Flash class provides the duration of a single identified component of the flash for the PIXL MCC illumination.

Name: device_name
Description: The device_name attribute supplies the formal name for an imaging instrument, an imaging instrument device, or some point on the instrument or device.

Name: flash_duration
Description: The flash_duration attribute provides the duration of a single component of the flash for the PIXL MCC illumination.

Name: Device_Flashes
Description: The Device_Flashes class provides a container for the set of flash durations for the PIXL MCC illumination.

Name: Device_Temperature
Description: The Device_Temperature class provides a container for the temperature of some point on an imaging instrument or other imaging device.

Name: device_name
Description: The device_name attribute supplies the formal name for an imaging instrument, an imaging instrument device, or some point on the instrument or device.

Name: temperature_value
Description: The temperature_value attribute provides the temperature, in the specified units, of some point on an imaging instrument or other imaging instrument device.

Name: Device_Temperatures
Description: The Device_Temperatures class provides a container for the set of temperatures of an imaging instrument or other imaging device.

Name: Device_Voltage
Description: The Device_Voltage class provides the voltage of some point on an imaging instrument or other imaging device.

Name: device_name
Description: The device_name attribute supplies the formal name for an imaging instrument, an imaging instrument device, or some point on the instrument or device.

Name: voltage_value
Description: The voltage_value attribute provides provides the voltage, in the specified units, of an imaging instrument or some part of the imaging instrument.

Name: Device_Voltages
Description: The Device_Voltage class provides a container for the set of voltages of an imaging instrument or other imaging device.

Name: PIXL_Illumination
Description: Container class containing information related to the illumination devices on PIXL. There are two, flood light and structured light. Note that some of the illumination is in the img:Illumination class; the information here is instrument-specific information that does not fit into the img: framework.

Name: PIXL_Compression
Description: The PIXL Compression class provides information about the compression applied to the data product.

Name: inst_compression_mode
Description: The inst_compression_mode identifies the type of compression applied to a data product.

Name: inst_compression_name
Description: The inst_compression_name gives the name of the compression algorithm applied to a data product.

Name: PIXL_Parameters
Description: The PIXL Parameters class provides metadata specific to PIXL observations.

Name: pixl_motion_counter
Description: The PIXL Motion Counter is a counter representing a change to the PIXL Hexapod position. The counter starts at 0 when PIXL is powered on (presumably with the hexapod in the "homed" position) and increases by 1 each time the hexapod is moved.

Name: pixl_rtt
Description: The pixl_rtt attribute is the PIXL-specific 9-character Round-Trip Tracking code. A specific pixl_rtt value is assigned to all products collected during the same PIXL observation set. The pixl_rtt value also appears in characters 36-44 of the PIXL data file name. The code is typically a string of digits with leading zeroes.

Name: pdp_category
Description: The pdp_category identifies the PIXL data product category number.

Name: pdp_category_name
Description: The pdp_category_name identifies the PIXL data product category name.

Name: pdp_size
Description: The pdp_size gives the size of the PIXL data product as it was stored in Non-Volatile Memory.

Name: pdp_nvm_usn
Description: The pdp_nvm_usn gives the Universal Sequence Number of the data product as it was stored in Non-Volatile Memory.

Name: pdp_nvm_chunks
Description: The pdp_nvm_chunks gives the number of Non Volatile Memory chunks that make up a PIXL data product.

Name: pdp_nvm_block
Description: The pdp_nvm_block identifies the Non Volatile Memory block from which Anomalous Retrieved data was read. Applies only to anomalous data.

Name: pdp_nvm_page
Description: The pdp_nvm_page identifies the page in Non Volatile Memory from which Anomalous Retrieved Data was read. Applies only to anomalous data.

Name: RIMFAX_Parameters
Description: Container for the attributes describing a RIMFAX observation

Name: config_id
Description: Identifier of current RIMFAX configuration mode

Name: decimation
Description: Onboard decimation of acquired soundings, in number of soundings removed per each sounding downlinked.

Name: setup_file
Description: Name of the setup file.

Name: calibration
Description: True if the radar is connected to the calibration cable, false if it is connected to the antenna cable.

Name: gate_frequency
Description: Frequency of the gate signal

Name: number_of_samples
Description: Number of samples in each sounding.

Name: number_of_sweeps
Description: Number of sweeps that are integrated internally in the radar.

Name: receive_only
Description: True if the radar is in passive mode, false if it is in active (normal radar) mode.

Name: rx_delay
Description: Time delay of receiver gate

Name: rx_attenuation
Description: Attenuation in the receive path; higher values represent more dampening of the received signal

Name: start_frequency
Description: Start frequency of recorded bandwidth range (same as stop_frequency for single-frequency Passive Meas)

Name: stop_frequency
Description: Stop frequency of recorded bandwidth range (same as start_frequency for single-frequency Passive Meas)

Name: sweep_time
Description: Duration of radar-signal generation sweep through frequency bandwidth, for Active Meas; Duration of receive-only sweep through frequency bandwidth, for Passive Meas

Name: tx_delay
Description: Time delay of transmitter gate

Name: tx_attenuation
Description: Attenuation in the transmit path, higher values represent lower output power

Name: group_spacing
Description: Distance between sounding groups (i.e. distance between soundings of a given mode) as set in activity uplink (actual distance may deviate slightly); 0 if not a Traverse sounding

Name: sinetable
Description: Sine table used to create the radar bandwidth sweep.

Name: lis_soundings
Description: The number of soundings in a Long Integration Sounding (LIS) observation.

Name: note
Description: This note field can be used to indicate that the attenuation values are in dB because there is no unit_of_measure for such units.

Name: start_utc
Description: Start time in UTC of first activity in the data product

Name: stop_utc
Description: Stop time in UTC of last activity in the data product

Name: start_jdate
Description: Start time in Julian date of first activity in the data product

Name: stop_jdate
Description: Stop time in Julian date of last activity in the data product.

Name: start_sounding_counter
Description: Start value of sounding counter of first activity in the data product. The sounding counter records absolute total count of soundings since start of M2020 mission.

Name: stop_sounding_counter
Description: Stop value of sounding counter of last activity in the data product. The sounding counter records absolute total count of soundings since start of M2020 mission.

Name: min_rover_lat
Description: The minimum value of rover_lat, the planetocentric latitude of the rover RNAV frame origin

Name: max_rover_lat
Description: The maximum value of rover_lat, the planetocentric latitude of the rover RNAV frame origin

Name: min_rover_lon
Description: The minimum value of rover_lon, the east longitude of the rover RNAV frame

Name: max_rover_lon
Description: The maximum value of rover_lon, the east longitude of the rover RNAV frame

Name: min_rover_elev
Description: The minimum value of rover_elev, the planetary elevation of the rover RNAV frame origin

Name: max_rover_elev
Description: The maximum value of rover_elev, the planetary elevation of the rover RNAV frame origin

Name: Calibration_Target
Description: The Calibration_Target class contains information about the target of a calibration measurement.

Name: calibration_target_number
Description: The calibration_target_name gives the number of the calibration target as defined in the SHERLOC instrument paper, Bhartia et al., SSR, 2020. Each calibration target number is associated with a calibration target name: (0) Not Applicable (1) AlGaN on Sapphire 264 nm (2) Diffusil Diffuser (3) Mars Meteorite SAU 008 (4) Intensity Target (5) AlGaN on Sapphire 340 nm (6) Polycarbonate/opal glass) (7) Vectran (8) Orthofabric (9) Teflon (10) nGimat Coated Teflon

Name: calibration_target_name
Description: The calibration_target_name gives the name of the calibration target as defined in the SHERLOC instrument paper, Bhartia et al., SSR, 2020. Each calibration target name is associated with a calibration target number: (0) NA (1) AlGaN on Sapphire 264 nm (2) Diffusil Diffuser (3) Mars Meteorite SAU 008 (4) Intensity Target (5) AlGaN on Sapphire 340 nm (6) Polycarbonate/opal glass (7) Vectran (8) Orthofabric (9) Teflon (10) nGimat Coated Teflon

Name: SHERLOC_Parameters
Description: Container for the attributes describing a SHERLOC observation

Name: sherloc_config_file
Description: The sherloc_config_file provides the name of the configuration file used to process a SHERLOC data product.

Name: SuperCam_RMI_Mini_Header
Description: This class contains the mini-header" for the SuperCam RMI camera on Mars 2020. The mini- header is a set of information that is tightly tied to the camera hardware
Steward: and the instrument team finds value in keeping the set of mini- header information together. Much (but not all) of the information is also included in appropriate sections of the discipline dictionaries
Value Type: which is where general users should go. "

Name: rmi_header_size
Description: For SuperCam RMI this is the total number of bytes in MU and BU headers

Name: memory_bank
Description: For SuperCam RMI this specifies the Mast Unit (MU) memory bank used to hold image before transfer to RCE. There are 64 memory banks in the MU.

Name: rmi_cmos_registers
Description: Dump of SuperCam RMI hardware registers

Name: rmi_fpga_registers
Description: Dump of all SuperCam RMI FPGA registers

Name: marker_pad
Description: Static value used by the SuperCam RMI Body Unit (BU).

Name: rce_time_sync
Description: Last time sync value received from RCE by SuperCam RMI

Name: milliseconds_count
Description: Millisecond count from RCE time sync when image received from mast unit by SuperCam RMI.

Name: num_images_transmitted
Description: For SuperCam RMI, this is the number of images transmitted to the RCE.

Name: reserved_1
Description: Reserved field for SuperCam RMI mini-header

Name: reserved_2
Description: Reserved field for SuperCam RMI mini-header

Name: data_length
Description: Specifies the size of the image (in the telemetry stream) in bytes for SuperCam RMI.

Name: SuperCam_Ancillary_Header
Description: The SuperCam_Ancillary_Header class provides ancillary metadata specific to SuperCam observations.

Name: scam_point_number
Description: Point number in the raster

Name: scam_type
Description: Bit mask indicating technique type
A scam_type value of 0 indicates SOH activity type
A scam_type value of 1 indicates MICRO activity type
A scam_type value of 16 indicates IRSpec, IR-only activity type
A scam_type value of 18 indicates VISIR, VIS+IR activity type
A scam_type value of 2 indicates VISIR, VIS-only activity type
A scam_type value of 36 indicates TRLS activity type
A scam_type value of 4 indicates RAMAN activity type
A scam_type value of 48 indicates IRraster activity type
A scam_type value of 8 indicates LIBS activity type
A scam_type value of 9 indicates LIBSMIC activity type

Name: scam_two_d_flag
Description: Flag indicating a 2D collect

Name: scam_ldark
Description: Indicates whether darks were collected after LIBS active, before LIBS active, or both
No darks collected
Darks collected after LIBS active
Darks collected before LIBS active
Darks collected both before and after LIBS active

Name: scam_rdark
Description: Indicates whether darks were collected after Raman active, before Raman active, or both
No darks collected
Darks collected after Raman active
Darks collected before Raman active
Darks collected both before and after Raman active

Name: scam_rdstats_flag
Description: Logical to indicate if Raman darks are statistics

Name: scam_rastats_flag
Description: Logical to indicate if Raman active are statistics

Name: scam_ldstats_flag
Description: Logical to indicate if LIBS dark are statistics

Name: scam_lastats_flag
Description: Logical to indicate if LIBS active are statistics

Name: SuperCam_Generic_Packet_Header
Description: The SuperCam Generic_Packet_Header class provides metadata from the SuperCam product generic packet header.

Name: rce_time_sync
Description: Last time sync value received from RCE by SuperCam RMI

Name: data_definition_version
Description: Version number of the instrument command dictionary, which defines specifics of each command parameter, and the structure of individual data products like SOH.

Name: nv_xmit_buffer_count
Description: Non-volatile count of the number of times the generic buffer has been transmitted to the RCE. Acts as a unique identifier for the buffer.

Name: bu_software_version
Description: Unique identifier for the software version. Is a unix timestamp of when the software was built.

Name: cndh_firmware_version
Description: Unique identifier for the CNDH firmware version. Is a unix timestamp of when the firmware was built.

Name: bu_hardware_identifier
Description: Hardware identifier for a specific BU CNDH board. Used to know which SOH engineering unit conversion factors to apply to the data.

Name: se_firmware_version
Description: Unique identifier for the SE firmware version. Is a unix timestamp of when the firmware was built.

Name: se_hardware_identifier
Description: Hardware identifier for a specific SE board. Used to know which SOH engineering unit conversion factors to apply to the data.

Name: mu_version_identifier
Description: Version of the MU, response from the MU send version command.

Name: mu_hardware_identifier
Description: Hardware identifier for a specific MU board. Used to know which housekeeping engineering unit conversion factors to apply to the data.

Name: xmit_data_id
Description: The data_id parameter sent with the XMIT_DATA command

Name: reserved_1
Description: Reserved field for SuperCam RMI mini-header

Name: number_of_sections
Description: Number of command or data sections contained in this buffer. Does not include the header section or the trailer section.

Name: generic_data_buffer_size
Description: The number of bytes of the entire generic buffer. Includes commands, data, header, and trailer, every byte from the packet header marker through the Fletcher checksum.

Name: SuperCam_Parameters
Description: The SuperCam_Parameters class provides metadata specific to SuperCam observations.

Name: Mars2020_Parameters
Description: The Mars2020_Parameters class is a superclass containing all Mars2020 mission classes.
